definition.value: A butenolide that is furan-2(5H)-one which is substituted by a hydroxymethyl group at position 4 and a 2-hydroxyethylidene group at position 5 (the 5E isomer). A direct precursor of patulin in cell-free preparations of Penicillium urticae patulin-minus mutants J1 and S11, but not S15.
A sterol 3-beta-D-glucoside having 24-methylenecholesterol as the sterol component.
A 1-methyl-4-pyridone-5-carboxamide with 2 deuterium atoms replacing 2 hydrogen atoms.
The hydrochloride salt of SKF-96365. It is a TRP channel blocker.
An ether that is 2-(1H-imidazol-1-yl)-1-(4-methoxyphenyl)ethanol in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been substituted by a 3-(4-methoxyphenyl)propyl group.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of SKF-96365 free base.
